About this item

  • 14'' Exhaust Fan: Dimensions: 17.1 x 17.1 inch; Airflow: 1513 CFM; ETL Listed; Speed: 1600 rpm. Our high-airflow exhaust fan can eliminate heat, humidity, unpleasant odor, and dust from rooms, buildings, and small enclosed work areas. Get ready to relax and in clean air in all your rooms.
  • High Performance: 120V/60Hz, 30W. The wall exhaust fan has a premium EC motor that maximizes airflow while reducing noise and power consumption. And the fully enclosed motor has thermal protection and permanent lubrication for security and easy maintenance.
  • Smart Programming: We are equipped with an intelligent controller! Not only do you have temperature and humidity triggers, but it also allows you to set up to 10 speeds that will respond to changes in them. You won't miss a thing and will always be ready to adapt! There are multiple modes, allowing you to adjust as you wish. Timer and alarm modes are available on demand.
  • Rust-proof Material: The shutter exhaust fan has a rugged all-metal structure and features a powder-coated steel frame, aluminum alloy fan, and shutter, which is highly resistant to weather, liquid, and dust. It is perfectly suitable for any place you install and stays with you through the long, sultry summer!
  • Plug and Play: Get ready to fly through the installation process! Our wall mount exhaust fan comes fully assembled and ready to install right out of the box. Includes 4 bolts. You're ready to go by connecting the 5.6 ft power cord. No more worrying about wiring! Works well for garages, workshops, chicken coops, sheds, attics, greenhouses, etc.

Product Description

VEVOR Shutter Exhaust Fan with Smarter Control

What's the best way to beat the heat? Our Exhaust Fans are the quickest and most effective solution. Summer heat, humidity, and odors are dissipated with a single fan. Equipped with an EC motor and intelligent controller, the control with low energy consumption comforts all summer long!

Q: What size of hole needs to be cut?

A: You will need to cut a 12.8'' x 12.8'' hole to place the fan before installation. Fans can be installed both inside and outside the walls.

Q: How to connect these wires inside the fan?

A: No assembly required. Complete kit includes the fan unit, the controller, corded sensor probe, and power it through an outlet.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

5 Stars
Cools Off Attic and Excellent Value
I mounted this fan in the window of a 600sf upstairs rec room/finished attic space to move hot air out and keep humidity down in the summer. It moves a substantial amount of air and is surprisingly quiet for how powerful it is. The controller is simple, but not very intuitive. So it takes some time reading the manual on how to set up properly. That being said, once it's set up, it provides great exhaust, keep the space cooler and less humid.

djbzz
5.0 out of 5 stars 14" Fan Good fan, challenging install
Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
Style: w/ Temperature Humidity Controller Exhaust FanSize: 14 InchVerified Purchase
Put the 14" fan in my garage to pull out summer heat. Fan works well, price is right. Used Timer and Temp functions, which seem accurate. Had cut stucco and drywall, and the tricky bit was carving out the studs in the middle to fit the slightly large fan cage (tad larger than 14" stud spacing) Used metal and adhesive flashing, and caulked around the top and sides to make the opening water tight.
Overall, very happy with the fan, just wish the cage was a smidge smaller - that would have saved some time. Another oddity is that you have to scroll thru the controller menu to turn the fan ON. A dedicated ON/OFF button would be nice, but not a deal breaker.
